Package: dcvar
Title: Dynamic Copula VAR Models for Time-Varying Dependence
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Benedikt", "Lugauer", , "benedikt.lugauer@uni-leipzig.de",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits Bayesian copula VAR(1) models for bivariate time series with
    three approaches to modelling dependence dynamics: continuous random-walk
    correlation (DC-VAR), discrete regime-switching via hidden Markov models
    (HMM Copula), and time-invariant correlation (Constant Copula). The core
    single-level models support Gaussian, exponential, skew-normal, and gamma
    marginal distributions via Gaussian copula. Experimental extensions
    include multilevel models with random VAR coefficients for panel data and
    structural equation models with fixed measurement models for latent
    process estimation; these extensions have narrower diagnostic support
    than the core models. The multilevel extension currently supports normal
    margins only, while the SEM extension supports normal and exponential
    latent innovation margins. Estimation is via Hamiltonian Monte Carlo in
    Stan through 'rstan', with optional 'cmdstanr' backend support. Includes
    tools for simulation, approximate PIT diagnostics, trajectory extraction,
    fitted and prediction summaries, and LOO-CV model comparison for
    supported fits.
